name: anyjson
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "anyjson" %}
{% set version = "0.3.3" %}
{% set sha256 = "37812d863c9ad3e35c0734c42e0bf0320ce8c3bed82cd20ad54cb34d158157ba" %}
{% set build = 1004 %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  number: {{ build }}
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv
  noarch: python

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.6
    - setuptools
    - pip
  run:
    - python >=3.6

test:
  imports:
    - anyjson
  requires:
    - pip
  commands:
    - pip check

about:
  home: https://bitbucket.org/runeh/anyjson/
  license_file: LICENSE
  license: BSD-2-Clause
  summary: Loads whichever is the fastest JSON module installed and provides a uniform API
  dev_url: https://bitbucket.org/runeh/anyjson/
  doc_url: https://bitbucket.org/runeh/anyjson/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - kwilcox
    - matthiasdiener
